msgid "Linking Objects"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/creating_movements.rst:166
msgid ""
"Objects can be linked in order to create shared movements, that is to say"
" a movement that all the linked objects share with the parent object, and"
" relative movements, that is to say a movement that is the sum of the "
"object own movement and the movement of its parent object."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/creating_movements.rst:168
msgid ""
"As parent objects can be linked in their turn to other moving objects, it"
" is possible to define a complex hierarchy of movements."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/creating_movements.rst:170
msgid ""
"The hierarchy between objects can be edited by setting links that allow "
"you to set parent and linked objects: columns can be linked to other "
"columns, pegbars, table and cameras; pegbars can be linked to other "
"pegbars, table and cameras; cameras can be linked to any object in order "
"to create complex shots, for example with a camera following the movement"
" of a character in the scene."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/creating_movements.rst:172
msgid "Links can be set by using ports located around the object node:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/creating_movements.rst:174
msgid "The port on the left is for linking the object to another object."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/creating_movements.rst:176
msgid "The port on the right is for accepting links from other objects."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/creating_movements.rst:178
msgid ""
